nt one' - BexThey're not puppies.' -Cammie\n\n- Ally\n|\nA gift is pure when it is given from the heart to the right person at the right time and at the right place, and when we expect nothing in return\n\n- Anonymous, The Bhagavad Gita\n|\nYour time is limited, so don't waste it living someone else's life.\n\n- Steve\n|\nThis work was strictly voluntary, but any animal who absented himself from it would have his rations reduced by half.\n\n- George Orwell, Animal Farm\n|\nIn order to understand the universal perspective,first you have to know more than a version of truth.\n\n- Toba Beta, My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut\n|\nSometimes it's not always straightforward, but it's not always confusing either. You just have to respect a person's decisions without disrespecting them.\n\n- Temitayo\n|\nLearn the rules like a pro, so you can break them like an artist.\n\n- Pablo\n|\nTatsuya: What you have 'right now' won't necessarily continue on until forever...Hiro: ... Yeah, I know.\n\n- Ibuki Haneda, Koizora (Love Sky), Volume 1\n|\nOnce again, I've been thwarted by the massive difference between my vision of the successful me and the me I'm currently stuck with.\n\n- Lauren Graham, Someday, Someday, Maybe\n|\nPeople of vision must not be lazy, they must not be afraid of work, no matter how degrading the work might seem\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhy, I can't help wondering, is God thought to need such ferociousdefence? One might have supposed him amply capable of lookingafter himself.\n\n- Richard Dawkins, The God Delusion\n|\nWhy would anyone want to live in a cage when we are free persons? This is the point to make, when we can rattle cages it means we are behind bars and are not free.\n\n- Leviak B. Kelly, Religion: The Ultimate STD: Living a Spiritual Life without Dogmatics or Cultural Destruction\n|\nI think the essence of wisdom is emancipation, as far as possible, from the tyranny of the here and now.\n\n- Bertrand\n|\nWhen something or someone you dearly love is snatched away from you, something of you go with it. You become emotionally amputated\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Pearls Of Eternity\n|\nI've been to Canada, and I've always gotten the impression that I could take the country over in about two days.\n\n- Jon\n|\nI was wasting my time, praying for love.For a love that never comes, from someone who does not exist.\n\n- Morrissey\n|\nIf you believed in Christianity or Islam it was called 'faith', but if you believed in astrology or friday the thirteenth it was Superstition!\n\n- Jostein Gaarder, Sophie's World\n|\nIf we weigh the significance of a book by the effect it has on its readers, then the great children's books suddenly turn up very high on the list.\n\n- Laura Miller, The Magician's Book: A Skeptic's Adventures in Narnia\n|\nWhen the women begin to take an active part in the struggle, no power on earth can stop us from achieving freedom in our lifetime.\n\n- Nelson Mandela, Long Walk to Freedom\n|\nReal life is sometimes boring, rarely conclusive and boy, does the dialogue need work.\n\n- Sarah\n|\nPeter's destiny lay along a different path from John's. And your calling is unlike anyone else's. But the call remains the same: 'Follow Me!\n\n- Charles\n|\nThe truth was a mirror in the hands of God. It fell, and broke into pieces. Everybody took a piece of it, and they looked at it and thought they had the truth.\n\n- Jalaluddin\n|\nBy changing your perception, awareness, and actions you create yourself again and again.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nTime has taught me not to lose hope, yet not to trust too much in hope either.\n\n- Carlos\n|\nThe same that oft-times hath charm'd magic casements, opening on the foam of perilous seas, in fairy lands forlorn.\n\n- John\n|\nOf the four wars in my lifetime, none came about because the U.S. was too strong.\n\n- Ronald\n|\nHope is not the conviction that something will turn out well, but the certainty that something makes sense, regardless of how it turns out.\n\n- Václav\n|\nNon sapevo controllare i sentimenti, li sentivo sempre troppo prepotenti e forti e mi ferivano.\n\n- Vanessa Vescera, Le parole di una Rosa\n|\nThe true character of a man is not seen through his choices, but the passion in his heart.\n\n- Robert\n|\nThree great lessons for my children; love God, love yourself and love your neighbour as yourself.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nHolding on, holding out and holding fast when the going is tough constitutes a winning mindset.\n\n- Ogwo David Emenike, You Are a Star\n|\nShe blushed and so did he. She greeted him in a faltering voice, and he spoke to her without knowing what he was saying.\n\n- Voltaire, Candide\n|\nI'd rather hear an ugly truth, rather than an obscure lie.\n\n- Ana\n|\nIf that church is not adding value to your life, you may want to reconsider how often you go to church.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nSometimes one has to know something many times over. Sometimes one forgets, and then remembers. And then forgets, and then remembers. And then forgets again.\n\n- Maggie Nelson, The Argonauts\n|\nIf you were born with the ability to change someone’s perspective or emotions, never waste that gift. It is one of the most powerful gifts God can give—the ability to influence.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nJust do it! First you make your habits, then your habits make you!\n\n- Lucas Remmerswaal, The A-Z of 13 Habits: Inspired by Warren Buffett\n|\nHope may have a positive reputation, but it has a vicious downside. If you have hope, you can be crushed.\n\n- Ann Napolitano, A Good Hard Look\n|\nRead everything. Read fiction and non-fiction, read hot best sellers and the classics you never got around to in college.\n\n- Jennifer\n|\nFor the briefest moment, Jack's face formed the faintest smile as he considered fear and anxiety, the latter two of which often caused people to forget what truly mattered most.\n\n- Jermaine Watkins, The Heart Train: Episode 1 of the Hartford Series Singles\n|\nThe purpose of life is not to be happy—but to matter, to be productive, to be useful, to have it make some difference that you lived at all.\n\n- Leo\n|\nA smile puts you on the right track. A smile makes the world a beautiful place. When you lose your smile, you lose your way in the chaos of life.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nWhen all seems dark and there is no light,Hope is the candle that always burns bright.\n\n- Divya  Singh, Of Heartbreaks and Hope\n|\nSwifts,flushed from chimneys, catch fire and swoop like blown sparks out over the ramparts and extinguish themselves in the sea.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nThere is no real world, just the one you create.\n\n- Jolene Stockman, Total Blueprint for World Domination\n|\nA person with victim mentality cannot find himself, his life mission, and go towards his aims\n\n- Sunday\n|\nYou'll find magic everywhere, even in dark, dusty corners, if you stop searching with your limited human eyes and instead feel with your naked soul.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nThus let me live, unseen, unknown;Thus unlamented let me die;Steal from the world, and not a stoneTell where I lie.\n\n- Alexander Pope, Poems Collected\n|\nIf you didn't remember something happening, was it because it never had happened? Or because you wished it hadn't?\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Plain Truth\n|\nThe paramount terror that plagues humankind is to live a meaningless life of an exile, an incomplete person whom fails to experience the rapture of living in an astonishing manner.\n\n- Kilroy J. Oldster, Dead Toad Scrolls\n|\nI have lost my faith, but I gained the truth! It is not important at all to lose your candle as long as you find a torch!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nWhen you come to God, the devil will remind you about the pleasures of sin\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThis is a good sign, having a broken heart. It means we have tried for something.\n\n- Elizabeth Gilbert, Eat, Pray, Love\n|\nEven if you become the most perfect version of yourself, someone will find something negative to say.\n\n- T.C.\n|\nYou were born of two flawed yet beautiful souls. Happiness is your birthright, and love is your guide.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nMen are made for happiness, and he who is completely happy has the right to say to himself, 'I am doing God's will on earth.\n\n- Fyodor Dostoyevsky, The Brothers Karamazov\n|\nA man may die, nations may rise and fall, but an idea lives on. Ideas have endurance without death.\n\n- John\n|\nLife without love, is the soul without the spirit.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nIf you cannot change the reality of other people, their reality will become yours.\n\n- Sean Azimov, The True Language Of Love: The Book Of Life\n|\nSince I was young, I have always known this: Life damages us, every one. We can’t escape that damage. But now, I am also learning this: We can be mended. We mend each other\n\n- Veronica\n|\nA poet is an artist that paints pictures by mixing thought, imagination, and emotion with words.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI live not in myself, but I becomePortion of that around me: and to meHigh mountains are a feeling, but the humof human cities torture.\n\n- George Gordon Byron, Childe Harold's Pilgrimage\n|\nCauldron save you.Mother hold you.Pass through the gates, and smell that immortal land of milk and honey.Fear no evil.Feel no pain.Go, and enter eternity.\n\n- Sarah J. Maas, A Court of Thorns and Roses"